# S05-T01: Start Screen

## Objective
`StartScreen` — title card with game name, tagline, CTA button, and a decorative
assistive piano keyboard. Triggers audio preload on mount. GSAP entrance animation.

## Acceptance Criteria
- `getNoteFinderKeyboardAudioEngine().preload()` called on mount.
- Title and CTA animate in with GSAP stagger on mount.
- CTA button hover: GSAP scale 1.05, shadow-lift-orange.
- Decorative keyboard: `<PianoKeyboard variant="assistive" ...>` (display-only).
- Layout works on 375px mobile.

## Steps
1. Create `src/screens/StartScreen.tsx`.
2. Props: `onStart: () => void`.
3. `useEffect([], () => { getNoteFinderKeyboardAudioEngine().preload() })`.
4. GSAP stagger entrance on mount: `gsap.from([titleRef, taglineRef, btnRef], { y:30, autoAlpha:0, stagger:0.12, duration:0.5, ease:'power3.out' })`.
5. Layout: centered column, game background visible, `glass-panel` card.
6. Title: "🎵 MuseCool" in `text-4xl font-black text-neutral`.
7. Tagline: "Can you find the note?" in `text-secondary`.
8. CTA: `bg-primary text-white font-bold rounded-2xl px-8 py-4 text-xl shadow-lift-orange`.
9. Decorative keyboard below: range `lowMidi={60} highMidi={71}` (C4–B4 only).
10. `git commit -m "feat: StartScreen"`.
